caption.text:
Today is specifically dedicated to my great grandparents. We went to Suliki (also known as the hometown of Tan Malaka ha) visited the abandoned house they used to live in, met the elders who knew them (I had to use my rusty Minang-tongue lol since they don't speak Indonesian), and we spent our day surrounded by beautiful ricefields and hills!

They told us stories and showed us photos of the two of them, Datuk Bahyus and Nenek Sofia. Bunda said if Datuk is alive today, he would like me very much bcs he likes active and talkative girls like the two of us haha üòÇ He sure got some swagggg on him! Check my stories to see his photo teehee~

Everyone still miss them everyday there. I think I know them better now, thanks to today. Today was pleasant, I'm so happy üòä Alhamdulillahüíï

caption.text:
Why does one travel? Some travels to escape, to boast (in sosyel media lol), to discover, to meet new people, to see other culture, to eat (me hehe). Others began to feel that travelling is overrated. That millenials spent ridiculous amount of money for what they call "experience". That we should invest our time, money and energy on something more beneficial. Well that's not completely wrong.
-
You can find escape in a lot of mundane things like reading, writing, seeing your loved ones, a cup of tea, and sorts. So yeah, travelling is not the only way to do it, but when I do, I take brain pictures (and real ones lol), I thank God for the wonderful sights, and I tend to see the beauty in realizing the grandness of our Creator, how little and powerless we actually are. Humans credit themselves more than they should. It's what lead people from old times believe we're the center of the universe. That the world is created for us only and it is ours, when in fact it will still be beautiful without our presence.
-
Maybe it's good to escape once in a while, (or at the very least be a mind-wanderer lol). And when you're back to your daily boring stuffs, always remember the places out there waiting for you to visit or return! At least that's how I get by haha.... Let's go on an adventure and may we cross paths!
-
Photos taken from my previous visit to #TanjungAan, #Lombok and #GiliTrawangan in July 2014 right before osjur lol

caption.text:
I'm so happy with #JJF2017 Sunday's setlist and guess what, no special show! So you get to see headline artists like Sergio Mendes and Ne-Yo with a mere daily pass, huzzah! (Fun fact! Mr. Mendes performed in JJF special show 10 years ago)
Our setlist were:

1. Goodluck Heiwa, this bubbly and jumpy jazz duo from Japan whose venue got some cozy pillows for us to lay around teeheehee
2. Fareed Haqueüé∏ Feat. Tony Monaco üéπ, these energized uncles! Look at how crazy Mr. Monaco was üòÇ I can't even
3. Paulinho Garcia, this soloist took me back to my bimbel days where I would listen to KLCBS fm while studying for ITB, that's how I know most of the songs he played which were some brazilian bossa nova classics lol
4. Richard Bona and Mandekan Cubano, I had the chance to check them out while waiting for Mezzoforte, how can I not when these guys are that awesome! Their music is kinda the stuffs my dad would listen to~
5. Mezzoforte, these classy gentlemen was Zia's pick. Time to swift from latin musics to fusion, my mom would totally dig them! Also heating up our fusion earbuds for the next artist:
6. Chick Corea Elektic Band!!!! Their show was sooooo crowded despite the humongous hallüî• that we had to stand in the back. Here Mr. Corea guides us singing to their last song (I kept silent bcs I lost my voice lol) 
7. Anddd MY JJF GOALS: SERGIO MENDES!!! I've listened to him since 5th grade, this grammy winner sure knows how to put together a team and a show! Pardon the shaky video for my legs can't stand not to danceüíÉ
8. Bebel Gilberto, I thought we'd miss her show since we lost track of time in Mr. Mendes', but her show got delayed too so we get to see her untill my fav song! Her summer samba will swing you away~
9. Incognito, this JJF regular is so diverse! In the middle of the show Mr. Maunick took the time to promote a small orphanage in Kupang and by the end of the show he made a powerful speech of love and the gang hug each other on stage while singing Bob Marley's One Love, awwww!
-
Last but not least, an appreciation pic for Zia and Aldi who's crazy enough to go despite having midterm exam the next day(!!!) Thanku fellas, can't make it without yallüò¢

March would've been a really ugly month if there's no Java Jazz Festival on it. I kinda want to do a super late JJF higlights post(s) before the month ends. Too lazy to sort and pick out stuffs so thanks instagram's multiple post teehee. Pls üêª with me lol, we'll see how that'll turn out! #JJF2017

This experience almost got spiritual.

I was looking for my brother, and when look into my right theres this big old sea turtle who just swam by me. 
I wanna stay there and watch and be mesmerized but then he would miss this. So I went back a few seconds to go fetch him and then swim the hell forward to catch this sight.

We stopped when we reached the cliff between the corals area and the deeper sea. Many says we're really lucky to see it. We can't say anything more than, Alhamdulillah, God is grand :')
